{
  "texts": [
    "One molecule stood out for its potent inhibitory activity and ideal ADMET properties.",
    "In this article, we have explored a range of Artificial Intelligence (AI) methodologies applied in drug design.",
    "Currently, the field is evolving, with these methodologies primarily applied in experimental settings.",
    "To date, the results, while promising in accelerating and standardizing drug optimization for known targets, have not substantially led to the creation of novel de novo structures with distinct inhibition patterns from existing inhibitors.",
    "The aspiration to simplify and automate drug design for new targets or novel targeting patterns remains largely unfulfilled."
  ]
}